@Jovieta-w3c Yes. If anyone wants to see another scenario of such there is a Tv mini series from the early 80s simply called WWIII. It starred David Soul from Starsky and Hutch. Its a bit dated but its still brilliant. Russia sneaks a team into Alaska to cut an oil pipeline and blackmail America into restoring grain shipments (like the sanctions America just put on Russia) that they are using to try to control Soviet Russia. Things escalate steadily, going from America not believing the Russians could do such a thing, to sending their own team to counter them that is un prepared, to a shooting war and stand off at the pumping station they are trying to take. Meanwhile the President is trying to deal with the Russians who deny its happening at all. And it builds and builds. Till the final part where each side is lying to the other while preparing to strike. The series ends on a montage of people going about their lives, unaware they are about to blasted to oblivion, and slowly the noise of bombers etc overlays it till it freezeframes and ends just like House of Dynamite. 
At the time when it was broadcast I was upset it had not had a resolution, not understanding that was the point. As everyone was going to die. The end of the world.

There was supposed to be a follow up series covering the events / President etc and how he would deal with the aftermath, but in the end it never happened. As there would be no one to deal with anything....

